Personnaly, I prefer Syslog from www.clarkware.com
&lt;http://www.clarkware.com&gt; .  JavaWorld ( www.javaworld.com
&lt;http://www.javaworld.com&gt; ) had an article about best practices for it.

What I like about Syslog (although I have not used Log4J very much) is that
I can start logging with just a line.  The default values are fine for me -
Output goes to the console.

The only problem I have with that is that the results of the output are not
mixed with the results of the TestCase.  So, if I have lots of debugging
messages, the output is not with the failure.  I have to work a bit to make
it fit.  But it&#39;s usually paid off by finding another error or two :)

Thanks,
Francois

